        "title": "fix(telegram): suppress message-tool reply previews",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRefs #80520.\n\nFixes Telegram turns where visible source replies resolve to message-tool-only delivery but Telegram still created transient draft/reasoning previews before core suppressed source delivery.\n\n- Share the harness `sourceVisibleReplies` default resolver used by core dispatch.\n- Share the message-tool availability policy check so Telegram's pre-dispatch decision matches core fallback behavior.\n- Suppress Telegram partial/reasoning previews only when source delivery actually remains `message_tool_only`.\n- Preserve automatic previews for explicit commands and for restrictive tool-policy fallback.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: Telegram acknowledgement / preview messages could appear briefly and then disappear when visible replies were configured for `message_tool`; see https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/80520#issuecomment-4510305367.\n- Real environment tested: Reporter-provided real Telegram direct-message proof on May 22, 2026, plus maintainer local and AWS Crabbox validation against the Telegram dispatcher and core source-reply policy.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Sent a real Telegram direct message asking for three test messages in a patched local OpenClaw install with `messages.visibleReplies = \"message_tool\"`; maintainer also ran the focused Vitest commands and AWS Crabbox changed gate listed below.\n- Evidence after fix: Reporter-provided screenshots and runtime-log excerpt showed three durable Telegram replies and no draft/delete cleanup entries during the patched proof window. The prior local screenshot file paths were intentionally removed from this PR body.\n- Observed result after fix: Telegram displayed the durable bot replies without the disappearing acknowledgement/preview bubble, and the reporter confirmed the disappearing messages no longer reproduced.\n- What was not tested: Full repository-wide test suite; changed-surface validation passed via `pnpm check:changed` on AWS Crabbox.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-telegram.config.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts` - 89 tests passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/source-reply-delivery-mode.test.ts` - 162 tests passed\n- `AUTOREVIEW_OPENCLAW_MAINTAINER_VALIDATION=1 AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` - clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- AWS Crabbox fresh-pr proof on exact SHA `312f6342a34ed8f0e129d81c021971358a3b91a7`: provider `aws`, lease `cbx_73ecd7fb2869`, run `run_33c2770f87d4`, label `pr-85403-freshpr-312f634`\n  - verified `git rev-parse HEAD` matched `312f6342a34ed8f0e129d81c021971358a3b91a7`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-telegram.config.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts` - 89 tests passed\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/source-reply-delivery-mode.test.ts` - 162 tests passed\n  - `pnpm check:changed` - passed\n",
